subtitleNullable: 150 years time series of full moon occurrences
descriptionNullable:
### Context
> There are exactly 1,868 full moons between 1900 and 2050.  

The full moon is the lunar phase when the Moon appears fully illuminated from Earth's perspective. This occurs when Earth is located between the Sun and the Moon and calls *syzygy*. The full moon occurs roughly once a month.

🌕 🌖 🌗 🌘 🌑 🌒 🌓 🌔 🌕

### Content

1,868 full moons between 1900 and 2050.  
The column Flag has special labelling:   
1. `[+]` Blue moon (second full moon within one calendar month)  
2. `[*]` At this point in time, a partial lunar eclipse takes place  
3. `[**]` At this point in time, a total lunar eclipse takes place   
4. `[/]` At this point in time, penumbral lunar eclipse

Time specified in Central European Time (CET) or Summer Time (CEST).

### Acknowledgements

All data was fetched from [Fullmoon Calendar](https://www.fullmoon.info/en/fullmoon-calendar_1900-2050.html). Here is my [repo](https://github.com/LSIND/advanced-python3#python-text-web-scraping) explaining how data was fetched.


### Inspiration

What this data can be correlated with? Floods or earthquakes?  
Or committed crimes?
